.TH SG_ENROLL 1 "2026-03-04" "sgpam 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
sg_enroll \- enroll a fingerprint for PAM authentication
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sg_enroll
.RB [ \-s
.IR level ]
.I username
.RI [ finger-name ]
.br
.B sg_enroll \-\-list
.I username
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B sg_enroll
captures two fingerprint samples from a SecuGen U20 reader, verifies
that they match at the chosen security level, and writes the resulting
template to
.IR /etc/security/sg_fingerprints/ username _ finger-name .tpl .
.PP
The enrolled template is later used by
.BR pam_sgfp (8)
to authenticate the user via fingerprint.
Multiple fingers can be enrolled per user \(em the PAM module tries all
templates and accepts the first match.
.PP
Each sample is attempted up to three times if the capture fails or
quality is below the enrolment threshold (60/100).
After both samples are captured, they are matched at the chosen
security level to confirm they belong to the same finger.
.PP
.B Confidence validation:
After matching, the raw score (0\(en199) is compared against the
threshold for the chosen security level.
If the score is below the threshold and the session is interactive,
the user is prompted to re-capture for better quality.
.PP
.B Post-save verification:
In interactive mode, after saving the template, a fresh scan is
captured and matched against the saved file.
If verification fails, the user can choose to re-enroll.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-s " level"
Security level for enrollment match confirmation.
Valid levels (case-insensitive):
.BR lowest " (30),"
.BR lower " (50),"
.BR low " (60),"
.BR below_normal " (70),"
.BR normal " (80, default),"
.BR above_normal " (90),"
.BR high " (100),"
.BR higher " (120),"
.BR highest " (140)."
The number in parentheses is the minimum match score (out of 199).
.TP
.B \-\-list
List enrolled fingers for the given user.
Requires read access to the template directory (typically root).
.SH FINGER NAMES
Valid finger names:
.RS
.B right-thumb right-index right-middle right-ring right-little
.br
.B left-thumb left-index left-middle left-ring left-little
.RE
.PP
If no finger name is given in interactive mode, a numbered menu
is presented for selection.
In non-interactive mode (piped input), a finger name is required.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Enrolment succeeded; template written.
Also returned by
.B \-\-list
(even if no fingers are enrolled).
.TP
.B 1
An error occurred (device not found, quality too low, samples did not
match, permission denied, invalid finger name, etc.).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/security/sg_fingerprints/
Directory holding per-user fingerprint templates.
Created automatically with mode 0700 if it does not exist.
.TP
.IR /etc/security/sg_fingerprints/ username _ finger-name .tpl
Enrolled template for the specified finger.
Written with mode 0600, owned by root.
Uses SecuGen SG400 format (AES-encrypted, approximately 400 bytes).
.TP
.IR /etc/security/sg_fingerprints/ username .tpl
Legacy single-finger template (from versions before multi-finger support).
Still recognised by
.BR pam_sgfp (8)
for backward compatibility.
.SH SECURITY
.TP
.B Root required
.B sg_enroll
must be run as root (typically via
.BR sudo (8)).
It exits immediately if
.B euid
is not 0.
The
.B \-\-list
option does not require root.
.TP
.B Umask
A umask of 0077 is set at startup so that the template directory and
files are never world-accessible.
.TP
.B Path traversal protection
Usernames are validated against a strict character set
(alphanumeric, underscore, hyphen, dot; max 255 characters).
Slashes and other special characters are rejected.
.TP
.B Template encryption
Templates are stored in SG400 format, which applies AES encryption
within the SecuGen SDK.
.SH DIAGNOSTICS
.TP
.B "SGFPM_OpenDevice \(em is the U20 plugged in?"
The SecuGen U20 reader was not detected on any USB port.
.TP
.B "Quality too low"
The captured image scored below the enrolment quality threshold (60/100).
Reposition the finger and try again.
.TP
.B "Samples did not match"
The two captured samples could not be confirmed as the same finger.
Run
.B sg_enroll
again using the same finger for both captures.
.TP
.B "Low confidence"
The match score is below the threshold for the chosen security level.
The user may re-capture or proceed.
.TP
.B "Verification FAILED"
The post-save verification scan did not match the saved template.
The user may re-enroll or keep the existing template.
.TP
.B "Capture failed"
The scanner timed out (15 seconds) or the finger was removed too early.
.TP
.B "Invalid username"
The supplied username contained disallowed characters or was empty.
.TP
.B "Unknown finger name"
The supplied finger name is not one of the 10 valid names.
.SH EXAMPLES
Enroll user
.IR alice 's
right index finger:
.PP
.RS
.nf
sudo sg_enroll alice right-index
.fi
.RE
.PP
Enroll with high security (score >= 100):
.PP
.RS
.nf
sudo sg_enroll -s high alice left-thumb
.fi
.RE
.PP
List enrolled fingers:
.PP
.RS
.nf
sudo sg_enroll --list alice
.fi
.RE
.PP
Interactive enrollment (finger selection menu):
.PP
.RS
.nf
sudo sg_enroll alice
.fi
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR pam_sgfp (8),
.BR pam (8),
.BR pam.d (5)
